The '''Bolton WtE''' is a waste power station constructed in 1971 in [[Bolton]], and is a major landmark of its skyline.<ref>[http://www.pbpower.net/whatwedo/gen/env/bolton.htm Bolton EfW plant] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050911092917/http://www.pbpower.net/whatwedo/gen/env/bolton.htm |date=September 11, 2005 }}, ''www.pbpower.net'', Accessed 27.11.06</ref> The incinerator burns up to {{convert|20|tonne}} of [[household waste]] per hour or {{convert|85000|tonne|abbr=on}} per year,<ref>[http://www.atlas.d-waste.com/ Waste Atlas] Facility: Bolton Thermal Recovery Facility</ref> and can generate up to 11&nbsp;MW of electricity. The plant is operated by [[Viridor]]. The Bolton incinerator is the only household waste incinerator in [[Greater Manchester]].

