{{Combined-marine-propulsion}}
'''Combined nuclear and steam propulsion system''' (CONAS) is used on the {{sclass-|Kirov|battlecruiser|0}} [[guided missile]] cruisers.

Complementary to the nuclear component there are two conventional boilers, installed as a backup in case of reactor failure. Both components are capable of driving two geared steam turbines, generating 120,000 [[Horsepower|hp]] (89 MW) at two prop shafts.<ref>[http://www.navycollection.narod.ru/ships/Russia/Cruisers/TARK_Proect_1144/history.html V.P. Kuzin, "Type 1144 Nuclear Guided Missile Cruisers", "Typhoon" almanac, 1-4 1999] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071123172928/http://www.navycollection.narod.ru/ships/Russia/Cruisers/TARK_Proect_1144/history.html |date=2007-11-23 }}</ref>

