The '''Integral Urban House''' was a pioneering 1970s experiment in self-reliant [[urban homesteading]]. The house was located 1516 5th St. in [[Berkeley, California]]. The founders were California State Architect [[Sim Van der Ryn]] and [[Bill Olkowski|Bill]] & [[Helga Olkowski]], authors of the ''City People's Guide to Raising Food'', and the project was run by the Farallones Institute (which Van der Ryn founded).
The [[Sierra Club]] published a book about the experiment in 1979. Elements of the home included a vegetable garden, chickens, rabbits, a fish pond, beehives, a [[composting toilet]], solar power and more.<ref name="Olkowski Olkowski Javits Farallones Institute">{{cite web |last=Olkowski |first=Helga |last2=Olkowski |first2=William |last3=Javits |first3=Tom |author4=Farallones Institute |title=The integral urban house : self-reliant living in the city |publisher=Sierra Club Books |year=1979 |oclc=644281567 |url=https://archive.org/details/integralurbanhou00fara |access-date=2018-08-27}} *''Reissued as'' {{cite book |last=Olkowski |first=Helga |last2=Olkowski |first2=William |last3=Javits |first3=Tom |author4=Farallones Institute |title=The Integral Urban House : self-reliant living in the city |publisher=New Catalyst Books |publication-place=Gabriola Island, B.C |year=2008 |isbn=9781897408162 |oclc=314432876}}</ref>
''[[Mother Earth News]]'' published an article on the house in 1976.<ref name="meniuh">{{cite web |last=Reynolds |first=Julie |title=Urban Homesteading: The Integral Urban House |website=Mother Earth News |date=1976-11-01 |issue=November/December 1976 |url=https://www.motherearthnews.com/homesteading-and-livestock/urban-homesteading-zmaz76ndztak |access-date=2018-08-27}}</ref>
