'''Recycled fuel''' is [[fuel]] made of residues as [[Carbon dioxide|CO2]] produced by using a primary fuel.

For example, CO2 [[pollution]] in the [[atmosphere]], produced by [[petrol]] burning or other sources, can be extracted to produce fuel through an [[artificial photosynthesis]] based in [[nanotechnology]], which helps to mitigate pollution, [[climate change]] and energy issues.

