{{British Indian units of mass}}
A '''tank''' is an obsolete unit of mass in [[India]] approximately equal to 4.4&nbsp;g (69&nbsp;gr). After [[Metrication in India|metrication]] in the mid-20th century, the unit became obsolete.

In [[Mumbai]] (formerly [[Bombay]]), the tank equalled 17 1/72&nbsp;grains (about 1.1&nbsp;grams), and 72 tanks equalled 30 pice. In the 16th century, the tank was reported to be 20.96&nbsp;g (323.46&nbsp;grain).{{Citation needed|date=April 2009}}

